messages.message: <!here> can someone take a look at a map records bug? https://alt.dogfood.instabase.com/apps/flow/edit/org1/repo1/fs/Test%20Drive/tests/general/single-flows/workflows/map-record-formula.ibflow# doesn’t work, but it works on dogfood. from what i can tell so far, https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/shared-utils/py-utils/ocr-client-lib/src/py/instabase/ocr/client/libs/ibocr.py#L130 is_record_populated always returns true, since the keys exist in the ibocr, but they are all set to None, causing us to try to run provenance tracking on it when there’s no provenance tracking info. Is this to do with ibdoc?
